obo:UBERON_0002421  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_5365  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3: immunogold EM imaging of ArpC2 (aka. Arp2/3) in mouse CA1 hippocampus showed localization to synaptic vesicle membranes and pre/postsynapse (distant from the plasma membrane and release sites).\n\n\"ArpC2 was concentrated in dendritic spines approximately 200 nm below the PSD (Figure 3F). However, a fraction of gold particles (~27%) localized to presynaptic terminals with a consistent and specific distribution. ArpC2 was overlapping with synaptic vesicles, but it also localized to the presynaptic area beyond the synaptic vesicle cluster, away from the active zone (mean distance ± SD, 298 ± 159 nm for ArpC2, and 173 ± 129 nm for synaptic vesicles). Very little immunolabeling was observed when the primary antibody was omitted as a negative control. In the few synapses that did have staining (<1%), there was diffuse non-specific signal across the synapse (Figure 3-figure supplement 1D-E). Taken together, the overlapping distributions of Rac1 and Arp2/3 at synaptic vesicles suggest a potential common presynaptic function related to synaptic vesicle modulation.\". Experimental description: Results, Figure 3 legend: \"Representative pre-embedding immunogold-labeled electron micrographs from 5- to 6-month-old mice in hippocampal CA1 for (C) Rac1 and (D) ArpC2.\"\n\nAntibody Anti-ArpC2 (rabbit polyclonal) MilliporeSigma Cat# 07-227;\nRRID:AB_310447" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-13" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5365" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

